    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-11T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-11T04:00:00-05:00" n="295"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/324</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in China</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-11T17:00:00+08:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram—Extract]</p>
                <p>Japanese Chargé d’Affaires reliably quoted as stating that his Government would
                    welcome an opportunity to participate in taking Kiaochow and that an expedition
                    for that purpose is available immediately. . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJVA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
